
[1]plain-dealing

   PLAIN-DE'ALING, a. [plain and deal.] Dealing or communicating with
   frankness and sincerity; honest; open; speaking and acting without art;
   as a plain-dealing man.

   PLAIN-DE'ALING, n. A speaking or communicating with openness and
   sincerity; management without art, stratagem or disguise; sincerity.
     __________________________________________________________________

